🛠️ Build Process

1. CPU Installation
- Installed CPU into LGA1700 socket
- Ensured correct alignment using triangle indicator

 2. Cooling Installation
- Applied thermal paste
- Mounted 360mm AIO radiator at top for exhaust airflow

 3. RAM Installation
- Installed RAM in A2 and B2 slots
- Enabled dual-channel configuration

 4. Storage Installation
- Installed NVMe SSD into M.2 slot
- Applied motherboard heatsink

 5. Motherboard Installation
- Mounted motherboard with standoffs
- Verified I/O alignment

6. Power Supply & Cabling
- Connected:
  - 24-pin motherboard cable
  - 8-pin CPU cable
  - PCIe GPU cables
  - SATA cables

 7. GPU Installation
- Inserted into PCIe x16 slot
- Connected power cables

 8. Front Panel Setup
- Connected power switch and LED headers to JFP1

---
 🚀 First Boot & BIOS Configuration

Entered BIOS and configured:

- Enabled XMP → RAM running at 6000 MHz  
- Enabled Intel Virtualization (VT-x & VT-d)  
- Set Boot Mode to UEFI  

---

 🐛 Troubleshooting & Debugging

🔴 Issue 1: PC Not Turning On
- Cause: SATA cable not connected  
- Fix: Reconnected SATA cable properly  

---

 🔴 Issue 2: CPU Debug LED
- Cause: RAM not seated correctly  
- Insight: Improper RAM seating prevented CPU initialization  
- Fix: Reseated RAM until fully locked  

---

 🔴 Issue 3: AIO Fans Not Working
- Cause: Fan cables not connected to motherboard  
- Fix: Connected radiator fans to fan headers  

---

 💻 Operating System Setup

- Created bootable USB  
- Installed Windows 11 Pro  
- Installed drivers:
  - Chipset
  - GPU
  - Network  

